<div style="background-color: darkblue;">
  <div class="container text-center" style="color: white; padding-top: 30px;">
    <h1><strong>SPM - Salesforce Package Manager -</strong></h1>
    <div style="margin: 50px 300px;">
      <%= form_tag search_path, method: :get do |f| %>
        <div class="input-group">
          <%= text_field_tag :q, nil, class: 'form-control input-lg', placeholder: 'Search Salesforce Packages' %>
          <span class="input-group-btn">
            <button class="btn btn-default btn-lg" type="submit">
              <i class='glyphicon glyphicon-search'></i>
            </button>
          </span>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container contents">
  <div style="margin-top: 30px">
    <div class="description">
      <h2><strong>Install</strong></h2>
      <div class="description-detail">
        <p>For Linux or macOS user</p>
        <pre><code class="lang-shell">$ curl -sL http://install.freedom-man.com/spm.sh | bash</code></pre>
        <p>For Docker user</p>
        <pre><code class="lang-shell">$ docker run --rm tzmfree/spm install {package_name}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="description">
      <h2><strong>Usage</strong></h2>
      <div class="description-detail">
        <pre><code class="lang-shell">$ spm install -u {user} -p {password} {package_name} </code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="description">
      <h2><strong>What Is SPM ?</strong></h2>
      <div class="description-detail">
        SPM is Command Line Interface to install salesforce packages that is managed as remote repository.<br/>
        It's simpler than officially supported packaging system. <br/>
        Because SPM is command line interface, you can combinate other *nix command.<br/>
        SPM can be also use as deployment tool. It can install from an salesforce organization to other.<br/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="description">
      <h2><strong>How To Work SPM ?</strong></h2>
      <div class="description-detail">
        SPM work with git and Salesforce metadata api.<br/>
        If you call install subcommand, SPM clone repository from remote and install it to your salesforce organization with metadata api.<br/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <a href="https://github.com/tzmfreedom/spm"><i class="fa fa-github" style="color: black; font-size: 50px;" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/tzm_freedom"><i class="fa fa-twitter" style="color: black; font-size: 50px;" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
